page.title: 08Junior Wing Cumbria Nat cons
page.content: My name is Jo and I belong to the junior conservation group called Watch. This group started with a small number of people and is getting larger and larger. We meet every other Saturday. Every mmbe ets a watch program listing the events for Spring/Summer then again for Autumn/Winter. Some of the activities we have covered ar toad counts, newt counts, and bat counts. Wildlife garden work, a fungus faray and a water bird survey. it was noticed that, because of the cold wet summer, the swallows started to leave earlier than usual. We all feel it is important to understand what is going on around us, and try to preserve it for the future.
